cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to reason about the intents and reactions of participants in events. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, it involves neural encoder-decoder models, which are commonly used in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also involves crowdsourcing, which falls under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of commonsense inference, which is relevant to the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) sub-category.
